==English==
===Etymology===
From Latin [[gravidus]] ‘laden, pregnant’, from [[gravis]] ‘heavy’.

===Pronunciation===
[[IPA]]: /'gɹævɪd/

===Adjective===
'''gravid'''
# [[pregnant]]; now used chiefly of animals, or metaphorically
